inn1.comm: good full delivery on off stump, Cook digs it out into the covers
a touch straight on a length, clipped down to long leg
too straight again, but gets away with it, long leg is up in the circle but Bell misses a flick and it runs off the pad straight to the fielder
this is clipped wide of that short long leg and they take two as deep square leg runs round in front of the Mound Stand
loses his line again and this time Bell flicks it fine of the short long leg
much better, full and inswinging onto the off stump, dug out up the pitch
on a length just outside off, Cook pushes without timing into the covers
full and swinging towards the off stump, Cook comes forward and blocks towards mid off
slides away from Cook, swings away a little, well bowled, Cook had a fiddle at it
fuller length, Cook stays back and dabs it to backward point
forward on middle and off, blocked back to the bowler
a touch short and wide, slashed hard down to long leg
very full on the stumps and Cook punches it very pleasantly back past the bowler, full blade of the bat and the timing is impeccable, runs up to the pavilion
length ball on the stumps, Cook tries to get inside it and flick to leg but it comes off the bat to the keeper
back of a length and it goes down the slope and beats Cook just outside off
and again, very nicely bowled, Cook a touch squared up, it wasn't far away from the off stump either
beats him again, good line this just outside off and Cook is rather poking at it awkwardly, not much you can do with that length
similar back of a length area, and Cook again nudges it outside off and misses
a foot outside off on a full length, left alone
tighter to off stump, blocked coming forward and pushed into the covers
back of a length, wide enough to leave alone again
a touch short and wide enough to cut, Bell gets it off the toe past point, not timed well enough to run it to the rope
this shapes in a little of just back of a length, Bell shoulders arms
length a couple of feet outside off, ignored
full length, movement towards the off stump, Cook is forward in defence
firm push outside off and a big outside edge trying to drive through cover flies past second slip, Mills at third man slides and doesn't get it back before sliding into the rope
back of a length just outside off, forced away backward of point
full and well outside off, umpire Illingworth lets him get away with one, on the guidelines that
this will be wided, full and it swings down leg side
full ball on the stumps, played with soft hands and runs it through square leg, long leg runs it hard but can't prevent the second
forward press on the off stump up to mid-off
blocked around the off stump on a good length, Cook stays in the crease
forward again, this time to a ball a little further outside off, pushed into the covers
sends this the other way and it leaves Cook who is not for the first time beaten following it outside off
fuller length, driven at but gets a thick inside edge via the pad into the covers
much fuller, clipped from middle stump and midwicket dives and saves nicely, good work
a touch wide of off stump and Cook is able to dab it down to third man
full and well wide of off stump, left alone, and indeed too wide
back of a length and straight, pulled down to long leg
length ball on off stump, played off the back foot towards point
full and swings away a little as Bell leaves alone a foot outside off stump
back of a length on middle and off, Bell walks slightly across his stumps and tucks to midwicket
shot! Too full and Bell plays a flowing on-drive, gorgeous, worth the entrance fee alone
back of a length around middle and tucked to midwicket, straight to the fielder
wide enough of the off stump to leave alone
covered up around off stump on a good length
dabbed from back of a length towards cover point
a little short just outside off, Cook whips it with a short-arm jab wide of mid-on, it runs down the hill and they get three
wide enough to leave alone outside off
good length but Bell able to shoulder arms again
blocked around off stump on a good length
touch straight, Cook able to tuck through the on-side for an easy single
middle stump line, Bell forward to push towards the on-side but it stops on him slightly and he just chips it slightly, very safe though
forward on the stumps, a firm punch to mid on
full on the stumps again, this time Bell says I'll have some of this and drive over the bowler's head, timed well, the outfield holds it up a little but it runs into the rope, great shot
now goes for a flashing off drive but only finds cover, that looked fabulous, stood and flashed the blade, timed it well but straight to the fielder
firm off drive on the front foot but mid-off dives across and saves what would have been four
this is four, too straight and tickled to fine leg
four more, full length wide of off, Cook gets a good stride in, hits on the up and powers it past cover, timing was excellent
similar delivery, a touch shorter, left this time
similar line again, feels for it and gets beaten outside off, poor stroke, reaching quite a way outside off for it
tighter to off stump, Cook up on his toes and dabs into the covers
length on off stump, blocked in the crease

full and wide, driven at and nicks it behind Southee does the job again in drawing Bell out to drive, it swung away a little and Bell got a thick outside edge which was safely collected by Ronchi for his first catch for New Zealand. Full and a bit of swing and Southee is in business yet again
full on off stump, blocked forward back to the bowler
forward press just outside off, blocked back to the bowler again
forward press again and ran back to the bowler
little wider and pleasantly driven to cover where it's well saved
forward on off stump, firmly punched back past the bowler, mid-on does just enough to save the single
length just wide of off stump, dabbed into the covers
a little too short and a little too wide, short point has no chance of saving that, cut with great timing
two feet outside off, ignored
full, another punch back past the bowler from a full length, this time mid-on can't save the single
covers up on the off stump
full and played forward, runs it out through midwicket
forward press on the stumps, back to the bowler from a full length
good length just outside off, played forward and runs it to cover
full length, driven at edged and gone and Southee's straightforward modus operandi does the trick again. Full and sliding past Cook who drives at it and edges to Ronchi who again takes a solid catch
length ball two feet outside off, ignored
similar line, a touch shorter, Root tries to stay back and carve it through the off side, misses
full on the stumps, Trott forward blocking back to the bowler
a touch fuller on a straight line, Trott clips it to mid-on

full on the stumps, clipped through midwicket, deep square leg is around to field in front of the grandstand, slides and, oh dear, flicks it back then it hits his hand and it runs into the rope, eeeeee oooorreeee
back of a length just outside off, dabbed down to third man
length ball around off stump, blocked up the wicket
a touch straight and tucked behind square on the leg side
length around off stump, played back into the covers
forward this time on a similar line, they consider a single in front of point but turn it down, running wasn't great between these two in the Test here
this time gets the forcing shot of the back foot in the gap and they take a run
too far wide of off stump to draw Trott into a stroke
full onto the pads of Trott, don't bowl there, well struck but finds short midwicket, who fields, spins and shys at the non-striker's end, Root was back and the throw missed anyway
full on off stump, pushed back to the bowler
length ball on the pads, clipped through midwicket
back of a length, blocked around the off stump, runs off inside edge and pad into the covers
back of a length around off stump, pushed into the covers
fuller, driven at just outside off, squirts it into the gully
short ball, pulled off high on the bat towards deep square leg, ends up taking the bottom hand off the bat
back of a length around off stump, tucked through square leg
reverse-swept first ball, doesn't get all of it, just a single as short third man goes to his left
swept hard from outside off to deep square leg
forward and pushed carefully to short midwicket
this time gets the push wide of short midwicket and down to long-on
now Root reverse-sweeps and misses outside off stump
skips down the wicket and flicks back to the bowler
back of a length down leg side and, oh, not a wide, must have brushed the shirt on the way through, Trott did skip across his stumps
this time Trott gets the flick away down towards long leg, fine of the fielder so they take a couple
full on the stumps, Trott goes to block and gets a thick outside edge to third man
back of a length just outside off, firmly driven off the back foot and well saved in the covers by McBren
length outside off, Trott stays back and tries to dab it to third man and only finds gully
off stump line, Trott forward and pushes up the wicket
flicked fine on the leg side and a chase for deep square leg down the hill, they run well and take two
a skip down the wicket and a flick from outside off to long-on
driven from off stump and the bowler dives and saves with his left hand
back across the off stump, pushing back to the bowler
driven slightly in-to-out and Franklin has to run around it at deep cover so they get two
full length outside off, flicked down to long-on
nice start, full just outside off, it goes down the slope and beats Trott playing forward
Trott gives himself room, Franklin sees him and fires it full and wide of off stump, Trott leans across and carves out to deep point
full ball on off stump, driven nicely past extra cover, deep cover in the game again
cut this time, only as far as backward point
defended in the crease, gets an inside edge onto pad, they consider and then decide against a short single into the off side
full on the stumps, Root moves down the wicket to meet it and flicks wide of midwicket, lovely timing into the gap with mid-on
length ball on the stumps, flicked through square leg
flicked with the spin again, gets it through square leg again
swept from well outside off to deep midwicket
length ball, tries to pull and doesn't get it, off the pad to short long leg
a step down and flick with the spin to deep midwicket
swept from outside off, misses, well wide of off stump for it to be lbw
hint of width and cut, Williamson fumbles at backward having initially collected it, so gives up a single
full outside leg stump, any touch and it's four and Trott gets something on it
back outside off stump, full length, pressed into the covers
around the wicket now, back of a length dabbed towards backward point and this time Williamson saves
full just outside in the slot to drive, Trott strikes it well having shimmied down the wicket, finds cover though
straighter line, whipped out through square leg
off stump line, flicked to midwicket
down the wicket and flicked with the spin to the 45
stays back and chops a length ball to backward point
down on one knee to sweep and gets struck on the pad
full on the stumps, driven down to long on
length on off stump, flicked with the spin to midwicket
full on stump, driven at, not timed, off the toe really to mid-off
down the wicket and slugs a back of a length ball through midwicket, again not timed but two as the sweeper goes to his left
driven from outside off, it was in the air for a time but he opened the face and steered it through cover
full length outside off Trott chips over extra cover, deep cover has to go to his right to field and they run hard to two
slower ball on off stump, patted back to the boweler
back of a length, pulled down to long leg
flicked through square leg from a full length on the stumps
full just outside off, driven hard to short extra cover
full on the stumps, blocked back to the bowler
length ball, flicked through square leg with the turn
fuller ball, pushed down to long-on
taken from outside off to long-on
nice-paced dobber in the slot outside off and Trott tees off like Same Torrance, whip-cracks a lofted drive back over the bowler's head for four to long-off
drags his length back a touch, goes across the stumps and tucks the ball through backward square
length delivery wide of the stumps, Root opens the face and steers one behind point
Ronchi up to the stumps now, Trott leans out and drills through the covers to the sweeper
here comes the Root flip (as distinct from the Buttler ramp), gets outside the line to a fullish ball, keeps the head down and flicks it over the keeper for a couple down towards backstop
gets forward to take a length ball through the covers for another single - good over for England, that one
pushes this down the leg side as Root tries to sweep and misses
tossed up, gets forward and takes a single to long-on
length ball, on the stumps and whipped off the front pad through square
floated up and punched straight back to the bowler on the walk

tries to be cute again and Root is bowled reverse-sweeping! McCullum tossed it up on middle and off, it perhaps hurried on a touch and Root missed trying to take the ball through the off side. Ring-a-ding-ding go the stumps
round the wicket, slip in for Morgan, he defends this from the crease
floated up and Morgan seizes on the length quickly, plants the front foot and clumps four out towards long-on
gets forward to defend a length ball
touch shorter and Trott sits back, opens the face and steers to third man
back over the wicket to a fellow southpaw, Morgan pushes forward to block outside off
slightly back of a length, again Morgan gets in line and defends
dug in short and pulled through square leg, rolling the wrists to keep the ball down
back round the wicket, this holds its line and beats the bat as Trott leans forward and dabbles outside off
floated up outside the line of off, defended coming forward
full length, skidding through outside off, Morgan crouches deep in his crease and hacks one low through point

scoops across the line and picks out deep midwicket, McCullum has another! Trott went looking for a boundary but halfway between a slog-sweep and a controlled paddle, the ball sailing neatly into the hands of the fielder a few feet in from the rope
tossed up around off stump, goes across and blocks
drops short and pulled powerfully through midwicket for a single to get off the mark
round the wicket, pushed through with the arm and solidly defended on the front foot
back of a length and rising at the body, Buttler does well to drop it short to leg and they scamper one as McClenaghan charges down to field

banged in again and Morgan swats across the line, a big edge balloons into the air and he's caught behind standing yards out of his crease! Think Mitch saw him coming, Morgan making a slight movement and then thinking about pulling out of the shot as the ball went away from him, taking the top of the toe-end and giving Ronchi his third catch
lovely first-up ball for the right-handed Woakes, from round the wicket and seaming a touch away to beat the bat
angled in with the left arm again and defended on the front foot
opens the face and gets a thick edge through backward square
on the stumps, takes a length ball through square leg for a single
tossed up outside off stump, driven coming forward but can't beat extra-cover
floated up on the stumps, worked towards midwicket
pushed through wide of the off stump, tries to drive on the up but can't squeeze it through
length ball outside the line of off and again Buttler can't pick a gap with his drive
full and on the off stump, clipped back to the bowler
very full and Buttler drags his bat down horizontally to skelp a single to long-on - just one off the over
length ball drifting on to the pads, Buttler goes across and misses but the ball rolls away for a leg bye
pitched up in the channel outside off, classical front-foot drive from Woakes but not really the connection to match

another classy drive from Woakes and some comedy runs into the bargain! This time he threaded the gap between cover and extra cover, it didn't have the gas to make the rope but Nathan McCullum, having reeled it in, slipped over in trying to throw to the bowler's end and it plopped lamely about halfway between the two... in the end they run four
Southee yelps energetically for an lbw appeal as Woakes walks across his stumps, tad on the high side though
good length, comes forward and defends outside off
slashes hard at a rising delivery wide of the off stump, a thick outside edge flies over the diving point fielder and down towards third man
tossed up on off and worked to midwicket with a close of the bat face
full and straight and punched back to the bowler
pushed through wide of the stumps, Woakes hangs back and flashes, the ball thuds into Ronchi's gloves
gets forward and manages to nurdle one past the bowler to long-on
short and sliding down the leg side, Buttler pulls hard but gets a mug of foam for his troubles
floated up and played back to the bowler
length ball on the stumps, punched back to Southee - who had overstepped
dug in very short and Kaboomed! over wide long-on, plenty of bat behind that swipe from Woakes and it drops a yard or two short of one of the longer boundary ropes
on middle and off, blocks back to the bowler
edged and dropped, though it was a fantastic effort from Ross Taylor, who seemed to hang in the air going to his right at slip, his fingers closed around it but the ball just managed to squirt free!
full and wide and cracked hard off the back foot, the man in the covers takes some of the pace off it
goes back and across and defends a shortish ball
short again and a bit of width, slapped off the back foot through square
tossed up and worked back past the bowler
floated up on the stumps, closes the face and takes one wide of mid-on
leaves the crease and punches the ball on the front foot to mid-off
on the stumps, gets forward and blocks
chopped into the ground straight back to the bowler
tossed up and worked through the leg side
good length, outside off, pushed to cover coming forward
pitched up and defended on the front foot
stays back in the crease and turns a length ball to midwicket
goes across and taps the ball towards mid-off - these two struggling to pick the gaps at the moment
good length and sliding towards leg stump, nudged wide of mid-on and they steal one
length ball wide of the stumps, chopped off the back foot straight to the point fielder
full and on the off stump, manages to steer the ball behind square
tossed up on around off stump, tapped into the covers
full and can't get this past mid-on
floated up, this time Buttler gets to the pitch and carves the ball past the fielder at extra cover for a boundary
drops short, Buttler frees the arms and cracks the ball towards N-Mac in the covers, who misfields and they get two
floated up and pushed back past the bowler
length ball outside off, punched to the fielder at cover
back of a length, outside off, stays back and dabs it short into the on side
short and outside off, Woakes hops back and defends from the crease
pitched up a little wider, opens the face and steers the ball straight to backward point

all sorts going on here, Woakes skips out in pre-meditated fashion, Mills rolls his fingers over the ball and drags it down, the batsman chips it short of mid-off and then has to hustle to slide his bat in as Nathan McCullum's throw just misses
pitched up outside off stump, driven half-forward straight to mid-off
tossed up outside the line of off and punched to mid-off, they pick up one

flatter delivery, Buttler tries to take it on, another reverse sweep and it loops straight to point! Frustration claims Buttler, who couldn't have picked out the man any better. Another wheel comes off the battlewagon
pushed through on off stump, turned off the front pad through midwicket
full and straight and again worked through the leg side with a turn of the wrists
floated up, bit more air, defended on the back foot
angled in and Bresnan again covers up his stumps
fullish length outside off stump, stays back, opens the face and guides to third man
length ball on the stumps, Bresnan pushes wide of mid-on

another edge goes to ground, Taylor's fingertips taking another bruising! This was between keeper and slip, Taylor admirably threw himself at it but the ball again eluded his grasp. Both those chances would have been screamers if taken
tight line and played back to the bowler coming forwards
bit of width, opens the face and picks out point
full and wide again, Woakes hangs the bat out and dabs another single to third man
tossed up outside off, gets down and across his stumps to sweep fine for a couple
full and tickled back past the bowler coming forward
short and sliding down the leg side - wide
suicidal run into the off side from Bresnan and only Williamson's misfield behind the bowler's stumps coupled with a slip sees him survive!
this skids through, maybe clips the inside edge and goes through Ronchi's legs, Bresnan wants another risky one and is sent back, again the direct hit would have seen him off
played back past the bowler for a single
full and wide of the stumps, hammed to the man at cover on the front foot
length ball, on middle and off, pushed into a gap between mid-on and midwcket for a couple
shortish and nudged off the pads through the leg side
slightly back of a length outside off and left alone
Bresnan gets across his stumps and whips a length ball through midwicket
Woakes using his crease well, drops back and again glides a length ball down to third man
pitched up full and wide of the stumps, Bresnan opens the shoulders and carves like your father-in-law on Sunday but bunts the ball straight to cover
floated up wide of the off stump, driven into ground and fielded in the covers
turned towards midwicket, can't get it through
full and gets forward, punched defensively to off
in the air but Woakes has bisected the two men in the covers, using his feet again and slapping the ball aerially for a boundary
this almost skips through, flighted up nice an high as Woakes again leaves his crease, he has to slam his bat down on it horizontally

sliding on and hitting the front pad as Woakes goes across his stumps... New Zealand decide to review the not-out decision but although the impact was in front of middle, the angle was taking it past leg stump
short and at the man, Bresnan chops across the line and pulls through midwicket

oh, Kelly, what have you done! Woakes attempts to hit Mills into the Abbey Road, he's nowhere near the pitch and it comes off somewhere near the bottom of the bat, sails high into the off side and is safely pouched by the cover sweeper coming in. England lose a fourth batsman in the 30s
touch short and pulled through midwicket for another single to Bresnan
banged in back of a length, wide of the wicket, Swann throws his hands and gets a bottom edge that bounces past the stumps and fine for a couple
length ball angled in, going towards leg stump, Swann attempts to flick and it comes off his pad into the on side
fierce lifter to end Mills' spell, takes Bresnan by surprise and he hastily jabs it back down on to the pitch
floated up, Swann comes forward, tries to play to midwicket and the ball rolls off his pad behind square on the off side
floated up and played back down the ground for one
flatter and this skids through and Swann drops his bat and misses
Swann gets across and works the ball wide of mid-on, the fielder has to scrabble for it and they pinch another
speared in towards leg stump, whipped through midwicket
floated up full on leg stump, Swann backs away and clumps it down the ground for a valuable boundary to long-off
length ball, comes forward and plays back to the bowler
beaten, stayed back and pushed indeterminately from the crease outside off
on the walk, Bresnan heaves across the line and a thick edge spirals out towards backward point, falling between two fielders, they get back for a second too
angled in towards the stumps, clipped through midwicket
very full, almost a leg-stump yorker, Swann tries to dig it out and misses, they get a leg bye into the off side
length ball, bit of width and hacked through point to the sweeper for another single
on the stumps, goes across and worked through square - that single brings up the 200, to polite applause
drags his length down a touch, Swann waits and pushes it behind square on the off side for a couple
opens the shoulders and lofts down the ground again, short of long-on for one
pushed through, swings across the line but can't connect
gets plenty on this, bit of tap from Bresnan at last, down on one knee and hoicking the ball through midwicket, beats the man running round from square leg
short and down the leg side, that'll be wide
tossed up around off stump and punched back down the ground
slightly back of a length, too quick for Bresnan, who plays and misses outside off
short and straighter, defended on the back foot in front of the stumps
full bunger this time, as Bresnan begins to advance, he jams the bat down on it - another dot
mixing up his length, banged in hard, this fizzes through as Bresnan swings like a rusty gate
another half-tracker, not as much grunt this time and thwacked between deep midwicket and wide long-on, Bresnan swinging like a rusty gate that's finally been oiled
very full, not sure Bresnan really picked that up, he gets his bat under it and spoons a single back over the bowler's head
back of a length and over the top of off stump, Bresnan has a big woolly yahoo and carves out a fresh slice of air
length ball on the stumps, this time Bresnan connects, lofting the ball towards long-on, it's quite fine but the fielder does well to prevent four
slower ball, inside edge and bowled him! Clever bowling from Southee, an offcutter duping Bresnan as he attempted to bombard the cows in their special corner
stays back and fences at a short-of-a-length ball that zips through outside off
length ball pushed across the left-hander, lovely shot from Anderson, hit on the up over cover and it has enough to get to the boundary, despite a despairing dive
Anderson backs away, Southee goes wide but inside the tramline and is called wide
Not too much damage done, though, as Anderson again swings and misses at one sliding across his bows
full toss, very wide of the stumps, Swann swats ineffectually and then squints - got away with that, did the bowler
full and outside off again, this time Swann steers it on the full to third man
on the stumps, Anderson shuffles over and chips one into the gap at midwicket
another wide full toss, Swann swings and misses again, it's right on the tramline and Aleem Dar says it's okay
dug in short and Swann clatters this high towards wide long-on, again the geometry is against the batsman so it bounces short of the rope but a useful boundary nonetheless
pitched up in the channel and Swann drills this straight to mid-off. A second wicket for McClenaghan ends the England innings nine down for what most will feel is a below-par 227

inn2.comm: full and leaving the right-hander, left outside off
full and down leg side
length delivery on the stumps, went to flick it to leg but missed, runs off the pads to cover

full and driven at edged and taken with a very smart grab at second slip, lovely catch from Graeme Swann. A duck for Ronchi on his New Zealand debut, he was trying to on-drive a very full ball but got a thick outside edge as it left him slightly, it went low to Swann's left and he got down very sharply to snap up the chance, very well held, it went quickly to him
full again on the stumps, pushed to mid on

another edge and another outstanding catch this time from Jos Buttler diving with one hand to his right, blinding catch inches from the ground. It was a full length ball just outside off, Williamson came forward to it and got a healthy edge which just carried to Buttler who got down in a flash and held it in the right mitt, superb catch and what a start for England
full on off stump, blocked on the front foot
full on leg stump, pushed to long leg
and now a leg side wide, ominous?
full of length wide of off stump, driven and a bobble takes it past cover, they take two, Bell just about managed to parry it
another leg side wide
length on off stump again, blocked back to the bowler
full toss on leg stump, clipped through square leg and long leg running round slides but can't save the boundary
length on off stump again, blocked up the wicket
a touch fuller, driven back to the bowler
full on the stumps, pushed into midwicket for an easy single
full outside off and driven with superb timing through cover point
tighter to off stump and driven without timing into the covers
drifts onto the pads, chase back for Buttler and they run hard and beat Buttler for the second
length outside off, really flies through as Taylor leaves alone just outside off
left again outside the off stump
length ball just outside off, pushed to cover
length ball closer to off stump, played forward up the wicket
off stump full toss, punched down the ground but too close to mid-off, Dernbach gets away with that
a little straight and clipped down to long leg
just outside off on a good length - don't get bored of that Jade - blocked up the wicket
overpitched outside off and driven again with elan through extra cover
full ball on off stump, driven to mid-off
goes to leave a length ball outside off but doesn't get the bat right out of the way and gets an underedge past leg stump
Guptill's turn to drive nicely, Anderson overpitching this time and that is put away delightfully through extra cover
touch shorter, blocked to point from just outside off
good length now, blocked into the covers from a foot outside off
touch shorter again, dabbed to point from just outside off
length ball shapes in a little and strikes Taylor on the thigh pad
firm push from a few inches outside off to cover
back foot now blocking around the off stump
couple of feet outside off, slapped to cover on the front foot
back of a length just outside off, blocked up on his toes
driven again from just outside off to cover on the front foot
pushed forward into the off side, wide off mid-off
back of a length, blocked around off stump
length ball outside off stump, ignored
left alone again outside off stump
length ball wide of off stump, Taylor flashes at it and misses, went right after that but it wasn't up there to drive
this is up there to drive and Taylor puts it away through cover point, nice shot
back of a length, Guptill takes it in the stomach, it falls on the off side and they skip through for a quick run
short and wide, slapped straight to point
back of a length just outside off, tries to force it away and gets it high on the bat to short extra cover
width offered and slashed hard backward of point, beats third man easily
a fuller, tighter line, driven but only as far as mid-off
just back of a length outside off, played from the crease with soft hands, guides it backward of square for a single
full of length on the stumps, played forward and pushed to leg
overpitched just outside off, driven again very handsomely for four past mid-off, no swing there
slightly pulls the length back a bit, pushed firmly at and runs it to backward point
good length on off stump, pushed firmly to point
similar line, blocked into the off side on the front foot
drifting down the leg side but gets a good chunk of the pad and Buttler is able to field
length ball just outside off stump, pushed to point
fullish length but Guptill stays back and gets a thick outside edge to point from a ball around off stump
short wide, see ya, hammered to the point fence
length ball on the stumps, pushed to midwicket

short and hooked, is there going to Bresnan? It is but, oh, he's parried it over the rope. He was five yards in from the boundary, had he been on the rope it would have been a simple catch but he was reaching back and could only palm it over for six
back of a length, pushed towards cover point
full on the stumps, flicked through square leg and that's four up to the grandstand
full on the stumps, pushed to mid-off's left hand, they take a quick single
length on the pads, runs behind square on the leg side
length ball, blocked in the crease, it runs away towards square leg and they steal a quick single
on the pads again, easy pickings down to long leg
85 mph, full ball played back to the bowler from off stump
short and wide and, oh yes that's right, cut for four, awful bowling
overcompensates and gets flicks through square leg
much better, length on off stump, pushed out into the covers
full ball on middle, flicked to midwicket
leg side wide
length ball, blocked up the wicket
just back of a length outside off and Guptll plays a really nice flick over square leg, picked that up very well and it runs down the hill
off stump, pushed into the covers from a full length
back of a length, pushed into the covers standing in the crease
very full ball on the stumps, dug out back to the bowler, Bresnan fields and tries to throw down the stumps, Taylor gets back
slightly straight and clipped to square leg
a foot outside off, played off the back foot towards point
too straight and flicked down to fine leg, poor ball to finish the over
length ball just outside off, goes to dab it away on the off side but plays it into the keeper's pads
tossed up outside off, played forward and blocked up the wicket
more flight outside off, clipped to midwicket
more back of a length now, pushed off the back foot down to long-on
length ball, covers up around off stump back to the bowler
stays back and punches down to long-on from outside off
length ball, played from just outside off stump, played to cover with a good forward stride
more of a punch against a slightly fuller ball to cover
foot and a half outside off, a flick at it and gets it off a wide outside edge to third man
length ball on off stump, blocked in the crease and pushed down to mid-on
another flick outside off, this time misses a length ball that just lifted outside off stump
played off the back foot with a firm punch down to mid-off
tossed up just outside off stump, blocked back to the bowler
straighter ball and flicked wide of midwicket
full ball wide of off stump, driven to mid-off
another drive, finds the same fielder
just outside off again, a flick back up the wicket to the bowler
touch straighter, played to leg and finds midwicket
full length on off stump, played forward and pushed out to midwicket
length ball on off stump, pressed into the covers
don't get bored with that Bressy lad, good length on off stump, played forward and defended a little awkwardly, gets it out on the leg side
little width outside off, a flashing drive to backward point
a foot outside off, blocked up the wicket
played in similar fashion
tossed up outside the line of off, gets a stride in and drives to mid-off
flatter and straighter, Guptill goes back and across and flicks one through square leg
angled in and not much spin, turned into midwicket  for one more
pushed through, slightly flat and outside off stump, steered off the back foot to backward point
floats this up high, lot of air on this and it dip in front of Guptill, who clips the ball on to his front foot trying to drive
full and floated up outside off, drives hard at it again and an inside edge loops safely through square leg, as Swann's mouth does a Cheerio
pitched up on the stumps and clipped through midwicket with a flick of the wrists
length ball, over the top of middle and off, defended back down the pitch
fuller length and around off stump, Guptill frees his arms and drives, picks out extra cover
back of a length again, dropped defensively short on the leg side
good length, outside off stump, defended into the ground in front of point
Bresnan maintaining his disciplined line, tapped short of mid-on and they go haring off for a run, would have needed a better collect and throw to have Guptill worrying
floated up nice and full outside off, steers it on the half-volley through square for one
flighted, around middle and off, clipped through midwicket to the sweeper
beats the edge, the ball drifting on as Guptill prodded, just inside the line and Buttler then attempts to whip the bails off too
comes forward, opens the face and steers a single into the covers
tossed up around middle and off, whipped to midwicket
goes back in the crease and turns a full delivery into a length one, chops it past the diving gully fielder and deep backward point has to run round
pitched up outside off and driven square through the infield
slightly full of a good length, punched coming forward to mid-off
angled in towards the stumps, Taylor leans round his front pad and nudges the ball wide of mid-on
touch shorter length, defended on the back foot, Bresnan collects
does him in the channel, this just drifts past Guptill's outside off, scrambled seam on a good length induces a false stroke
straight line, worked off the pads through midwicket for one more
floated and pushed back down the ground towards mid-on
very full, drifting towards leg stump and then shaping back slightly to off, Taylor gets the toe of his bat down on it and then opens his eyes wide a couple of times to refocus
another full delivery, tossed up high, punched wide of mid-off
flatter trajectory and defended outside off
pushed through a bit quicker, spinning back towards off, Guptill cuts off the back foot to cover
tossed up and dribbled towards long-on for another lonely singleton
edged and it flies wide of slip, pushed at it hard and they get a couple to third man
on the stumps, turned through square on the leg side
overptiched on leg stump and clipped over midwicket, it was in the air but well over the fielder and races away - that's Guptill's fifty and the hundred partnership too
flash and a miss outside off this time, bit of extra lift and Guptill gets away with it
full length and punched back towards mid-off
too full again and he latches on to this one, drilling the ball through extra cover for another boundary and 12 off the over
slow, looping delivery and defended back down the pitch
floated up and turned to mnidwicket
full and flighted up in the blockhole, punched to long-on for one
tossed up on off stump and driven back to the bowler
pushed through, covers the stumps and pushes to off
tossed up outside off and smoked over wide long-off, Guptill holds the pose and well he might, that was a murderous lofted drive
pushed back towards mid-off
bit of width and Taylor whips his wrists through another punishing cut shot that beats backward point and third man - half-century up for Taylor too
pitched up and driven back to the bowler, who collects in his follow through
very confident leave from Taylor, who lets a length ball go a few inches outside his off pole
too full and wide and driven again, doesn't quite get past mid-off, Anderson scrambling to get a hand on it but they charge back for a second
pitched up outside off and punched through the covers to the man in the deep
length ball on the stumps and turned to midwicket

he's got him, Anderson makes the breakthrough via a thin inside edge! This may have just drifted down the hill slightly, a lenght ball and Taylor was driving away from his body, on the up, the ball scraped a bit of paint off the bat before landing up in Buttler's gloves. A 120-run partnership has made NZ favourites but England have an opening
good length, around off stump, shows it the face of the bat solidly in defence
continues on a length outside off, this time Elliott shoulders arms and lets it through
digs this in very short, it sails over the batsman - called wide - and wobbles in front of Buttler, too, meaning he doesn't take it cleanly
is this ball reversing for James Anderson? Another length delivery curves back in, Guptill scissoring his bat down and the ball deflecting into the ground this close to the stumps
gets across and defends
length ball outside off, Elliott hangs his bat out, steers it wide of slip and they get two to third mna
pitched up in the channel and blocked coming forward
width again, opens the face and steers behind point
touch short of a good length, Guptill drives off the back foot through the covers to the sweeper
better line, angled in towards off stump and holding its line, gets across to defend
full and slightly wide of the stumps, Elliott gets outside the line and dabs it short on the leg side, they decide against trying for one
fullish, on middle and off, blocked into the leg side
in the channel, Guptill gets forward to a length ball and steers one into the covers running hard
slightly back of a length, shaping in and defended from the crease
good length ball in the channel, Elliott chops it towards backward point
gets forward to defend a good length ball into the off side
full and slightly wide of the wicket, Elliott gets a stride in, opens the face and guides a single to third man
length ball, around off stump, defended
full and well outside off, lovely flowing square drive from Elliott for his first boundary
dug in short and defended into the off side
on the stumps, turned behind square on the leg side and they put pressure on the fielder to pick up two
full, pretty much a leg-stump yorker and Elliott is thumped on the pad, Dernbach throws up his tattoo sleeves in appeal but it would have missed leg
fullish, drivable length outside off, takes a low outside edge and squirts to third man
defended in front of the stumps
goes back and waits on a length ball, shapes back in a touch and steered down to third man again
middle-stump line, Guptill goes back and nudges the ball off his pads through backward square for a couple
pitched up, pushed back towards mid-on
slightly back of a length, stays back and defends
back of a length, defended from the crease
on the stumps, worked with a closed face through square leg
length delivery, angled in towards off stump, solidly blocked into the covers
ooh, that was nearly a ripper from Dernbach, a fast yorker drifting in from outside off and Guptill had to react very smartly to bring his bat down in time
pitched up on off stump, punches a half-volley to mid-on

my word, what a shot that is, Guptill picking up a full, quick delivery on middle and leg and depositing it with interest over the long-on boundary. 'Lofted on drive' doesn't really do that stroke justice
floated up and defended around off
floated up on off stump, gets across and drives down the ground to long-on
full and flighted outside off, doesn't connect properly with the drive and it bobbles to mid-off
on the stumps and defended towards midwicket
full and straight, worked into the leg side
tossed up outside off stump, pushed back and Swann diverts it just past the stumps at the other end, Guptill then wants a run but is sent back as Elliott was trying to regain his ground
back of a length, gets on top of it and nudges behind square on the leg side
length delivery and played into the covers for a single

slower ball and Elliott is trapped in front! Or is he? He's called for the review straight away ... and replays show a big inside edge deflecting the ball on to his standing leg (which would in turn have made it miss leg stump). Not a great decision from Aleem, that
length ball, at the body, nudged round the corner for a single
pitched up outside the line of off, driven hard but straight to the fielder at mid-off
another slower ball - he's kept them to a minimum today - this time sliding down the leg side and clipped through backward square
tossed up and played back to the bowler
flatter trajectory, goes across and works one through mid-on
flighted on middle and off, tapped to mid-on
on the stumps, tapped to midwicket
gets a stride in and drops a length ball into the off side
floated up and Elliott gets forward and steers a single into the covers
length ball on off stump, patted up the wicket
a touch fuller a foot outside off, angled to backward point coming forward
short ball, hooked nicely, just a gentle controlled stroke to long leg
length just outside off, driven hard and they run well to get two wide of deep cover
length ball, tighter to off stump, played forward into the covers
forward on off stump again and pushed up the wicket
off stump, played forward back to the bowler
a touch fuller, dug out down to long-on
flicked with the spin down to long-on from just outside off
a step down the wicket and lifted nicely over extra cover, great shot
floated up again, flicked back to the bowler
whipped through square leg from a full length on the stumps
just outside off on a full length, angled down to third man
tighter line and punched firmly to mid-off
little bit of width offered outside off again and thrashed down toward third man, the fielder cuts it off and they take two more
little wider on the crease, length ball towards middle stump, pushed into the on side
firm press to mid-off and the race through for another single
length just outside off, dabbed square on the off side

floated up, goes to drive and gets done through the gate cleaned bowled. Went to drive from off stump but didn't get in a great position to do so at all, foot wasn't to the pitch, the bat was slightly outside the original line and went it turned a little and went down the slope, Elliot was done for, losing his leg stump
clipped with the spin down to deep backward square leg
stays back, waits for the turn and clips it out to deep midwicket
goes to reverse-sweep from just outside off and gets beaten, lucky it was outside off stump
shoulders arms outside off and it turns back not too far away from the stumps
forward press back to the bowler
length ball on middle stump, clipped out through midwicket
full on the stumps, driven with a slightly open face to get it past mid-off for a single
short and pulled off high on the bat, gets it down to long leg, slightly beaten for pace

McCullum goes down on one knee to try and swing it over the leg side, a nasty slog in the end and a bloody good job he got a thick inside edge onto the pad there, right in front he was, it runs down to long leg, horrible shot
a flash outside off stump, doesn't time it to short extra cover
full and straight, clipped down to long on
full and a little straight, runs off the pad to square leg
blocked in the crease around off stump
drifts down the leg side and brushes the pad on the way to fine leg, not great from Anderson
full back just outside off, carefully blocked into the covers
middle and off line, blocked towards mid-on
short and pulled behind square for four
full just outside the off stump, firmly pushed to short extra cover
a hint of width offered and McBren slashes very hard but straight to point

full and wide, swung away off a big outside edge and deep cover takes the catch and that ends a very curious innings from McCullum, he was thrashing awkwardly at a lot of stuff and has now holed out to Morgan running in from the cover rope, simple chance
length just outside off, driven with an open face out to the man at deep cover
length ball just outside off stump, dabbed into the covers
short ball, tucked away with a short-arm jab to deep square leg
length ball outside off, Franklin goes to square drive and gets beaten
tighter line, carefully played forward wide of cover for an easy single, told you Franklin was a steady head
slips down the leg side
flat delivery on the stumps, pushed down to deep square leg
played forward, pushed out to point from off stump
slides onto off stump, Franklin forward and pushing to cover this time
a skip down the wicket and a cool, calm and collected lofted off drive that is struck well, stick with me lads
back of a the hand slower ball, down leg side
length ball, driven from a tall position to cover
length ball that just drifts in a little, Guptill goes to drive and gets a thick inside edge up the wicket
slower ball again, Guptill watches it and pushes to point
full outside off, firmly driven just wide of mid-off for an easy single
short and whoosh, a big swing of the bat and it sails into the grandstand, didn't actually get all of it but clubbed enough of it
oh well bowled, fast inswinging yorker, beats Guptill, comes off the inside of the pad and deflects past Buttler too
off stump, smooth flow of the bat through the bat sending it down to long-off
tossed up but down leg
length ball on the stumps, Guptill stays back and flicks out to deep square leg
another lofted drive, over extra-cover this time and Bresnan chasing around the cover rope slides and makes an absolute meal of the save and ends up letting the ball roll into the rope
full length, calmly dropped into the covers
flatter ball, met on the full around middle stump, clipped to midwicket
full length again, dug out to backward point
length wide of off stump, swung away wide of third man for a couple
another ball in the slot to drive, only finds cover
bumper and called wide, ballooned over the batsman's head
back of a length, defended going back and across
length a foot outside off, Franklin stayed back and tried to guide it down to third man, ended up getting a bottom edge to the keeper on the bounce
tighter line and pushed to mid-on who comes in and throws down the stumps but Franklin is home very easily
slower ball, slogged down the ground, it's gone higher than it has farther and a diving Woakes back from mid-on just fails to take the catch, it went a long, long way up but Guptill survives
length down the leg side, tucked down to long leg, goes to 99
full ball wide of off stump, dug out into the covers
played forward, blocked carefully around off stump, that would do for Guptill
forward press on off stump to mid-off
good length ball angled across Franklin who shoulders arms
forward press on off stump to cover
length ball just outside off, punched to cover with a bent front knee

angled in, appeal for lbw, was this pad first? Not out given by Aleem Dar but England review but I reckon it's bat first and too high. Guptill just squeezed it onto the front pad as it tailed in a little. Indeed it stays not out
length ball outside off, Guptill pushes at it and misses, it runs through the legs of Buttler and nearly hits the helmet - which would have ended the game - scores now tied
solidly blocked coming forward on off stump
there it is! Short ball that he pulls through square leg and Guptill has his century and gets his team home
